data.name: Instant Pot Beef Stew
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty and comforting beef stew made easy in your Instant Pot, packed with tender meat and flavorful veggies.
detailedCookingInstructions: Turn on the Instant Pot and select the 'Sauté' mode.
Add olive oil to the pot and wait until it is hot.
Cut the beef into 1-inch cubes, season with salt and pepper, and brown the beef in batches, about 5-7 minutes per batch. Remove and set aside.
Add chopped onion and minced garlic to the pot, sauté for 2-3 minutes until the onion is translucent.
Stir in tomato paste and cook for another minute, scraping the bottom of the pot to deglaze.
Add the browned beef back to the pot along with chopped carrots, diced potatoes, thyme, bay leaf, and beef broth. Stir well.
Close the lid, set the valve to sealing, and cook on 'Manual' or 'Pressure Cook' for 35 minutes.
Once finished, do a quick release of the pressure. Carefully open the lid and stir. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.
data.modifiersForBase: Easy and quick using an Instant Pot
